  "description": "I went looking for this bird based on Greg Prelich's May 21 report, and I found it feeding in the seasonal marsh just south of Weld County Road 48. \u00a0It matched the description of a Hudsonian Godwit in breeding plumage: \u00a0medium-sized shorebird; long, upturned bi-colored bill; rufous belly; gray upper neck; dark scapulars; and gray coverts. \u00a0I also saw the distinctive black-and-white underwing pattern when the bird flapped its wings (not photographed).",
